**About the Protocol & the App**

1) The Protocol consists of a series of open-source smart contracts deployed on the Gnosis Chain blockchain network (“**Gnosis Chain**”) that creates a general framework through which users can mint and transact personal tokens, establish trusted connections, and engage in online communities. Please refer to the [Circles Protocol v2 Whitepaper](https://files.gitbook.com/v0/b/gitbook-x-prod.appspot.com/o/spaces%2Fs76GmMOXUUWWi7YK8Ugp%2Fuploads%2FeugvhtIIqA6IUW0aJKsw%2FCircles_Whitepaper_v220.pdf?alt=media&token=0ab0f75c-2121-4b47-a2e1-a2bd0eabd53f) for further information about the Protocol’s features and functionalities. The Circles Protocol v2 Whitepaper is referred to herein for information purposes only and does not form part of these Terms of Use. 

2) The App is available free of charge and can be accessed and used via our website: \[[https://app.aboutcircles.com/](https://app.aboutcircles.com/)\] (“**Website**”). Please note that although the App is made available free of charge, there is a fee mechanism built into the Protocol which applies when interacting with certain features of the Protocol. Additionally, blockchain transactions require the payment of transaction fees to the network (also referred to as gas fees). Please refer to section 6 (Fees) below for further information about fees that apply when interacting with the Protocol and executing transactions on-chain. 

3) The App is one of several interfaces through which users can interact with the Protocol to: create a Circles Account, send invites to others to join Circles, establish trusted connections with other Circles users, mint and manage personal CRC-tokens ("**CRC**"), as well as send and receive CRC within your trusted network. Additionally, the App provides users with the ability to interact with the Protocol to create online communities of Circles users (which we refer to as “**Groups**”), define Group membership eligibility, set a mint and redeem policy for Group CRC-tokens (“**gCRC**”) and administer and manage Groups (including shared Group wallets), each as further described in section 3 (Services) of these Terms below.

