Important Notice Regarding Data Permanence

3) “**InterPlanetary File System**” or “**IPFS**” refers to a decentralized, peer-to-peer file storage and sharing protocol that allows data to be stored and accessed using content-based addressing. IPFS is not controlled by a single entity and is designed to ensure data persistence and integrity by distributing content across a distributed network of nodes. Once data is uploaded to IPFS, it is effectively permanent and cannot be modified or deleted by the user or any centralized authority. 

4) Due to the decentralized and immutable nature of IPFS and the underlying blockchain technology, any information you upload through the App in connection with your Circles Profile will become **permanently stored** on IPFS and cannot be deleted, modified, or erased by us or any other party. This includes your username and any optional data you choose to include. 

5) By creating a profile, you: (a) acknowledge and accept that you are solely responsible for the content you upload; (b) confirm that you understand and accept that such content will be publicly accessible and permanently stored; (c) confirm that you understand and accept that this may affect your rights under applicable data protection and privacy laws, including your ability to exercise rights such as the right to erasure or data rectification; and (d) warrant that any data you provide does not infringe upon the rights of third parties and complies with all applicable laws and regulations. 

